	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65026367"><p>In the US yes, they balloon to infinity because (almost) every time we build a nuclear plant we build a new design. This would be like if a car maker only produced two cars every time they came out with a new car. The production costs get enormous when quantities are low.  We need to agree on a reactor design and stick with it.</p><p>
&nbsp; <a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2024/05/nuclear-power-climate-change/678483/" title="theatlantic.com">https://www.theatlantic.com/id...</a> [theatlantic.com]</p></div>
	</div>

